<h1>Help</h1>

<p>Welcome, quest writer, to the quest editor!  Here is the basics on how to use this (admittedly confusing) quest editor to create your own quest.</p>


<h3>Quest Start</h3>

<p>A <b>Quest Start</b> holds some information about the quest and what it takes for a player to be eligible to begin it.  Quests must all begin in a specific location.  Players can only complete a quest one time per player but are allowed to fail it any number of times and restart.  Additionally, players are allowed to abandon a quest at any time unless they have reach an end state, in which case they must accept the consequences of failure or success.</p>

<p>Quest Starts begin with a certain Quest State.  </p>

<h3>Quest State</h3>

<p>A <b>Quest State</b> makes up the bulk of a quest.  A quest state is a certain stage of a quest that a player can be in that contains a text description of what is currently happening as well as a number of choices (children quests) that the player is eligible to attempt.  As such the way to think about questing is a Directed Graph in which each state is capable to leading to one or more other states.  You can read more about directed graphs <a target="_blank" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Directed_graph">here</a> if you want.</p>

