<p>Some terminology you may want to know for this:</p>

<p>
    <ul>
        <li><b>Parent Quest State</b>:  A parent quest state is the quest state that a player passesd through to get to the active one.  The very beginning quest state, the one that the player enters directly when starting a quest, does not have a parent quest state.</li>
        <li><b>Children Quest States</b>:  Children quests states are all of the possible quest states that are possible to get to from the active one.</li>
        <li><b>Jumping to Quest State</b>:  Some quest states allow navigation to non-child quest states via jumping.  This allows a quest state to lead back to any other state no matter where it is in relation to the directed graph.  These can be used to bring multiple branches back to a common quest state or even back to an earlier one that the player visited.</li>
    </ul>
</p>


<h3>Quest State Requirement</h3>

<p>A <b>Quest State Requirement</b> is some condition that must hold true for a player to be eligible for an option that leads to a child quest state.  More than one quest state requirement can exist for a quest state; <b>ALL</b> conditions must be true for a player to enter it (a logical AND operator).  Quest State Requirements can be based off of a player's stats to allow unique options for certain builds or restrict others.</p>

